---
title: `$file->copyTo()`
description: Copy a file or folder to folder.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
->copyTo($folder = ROOT, $pattern = '%‌{‌name‌}‌%.%‌{‌i‌}‌%.%‌{‌extension‌}‌%');
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
File::open('.\path\to\file.txt')->copyTo('.\path\to\folder');
~~~

~~~ .php
File::open('.\path\to\file.txt')->copyTo([
    '.\path\to\folder-1',
    '.\path\to\folder-2',
    …
]);
~~~

Don’t be affraid to call the same folder name multiple times:

~~~ .php
File::open('.\path\to\file.txt')->copyTo([
    '.\path\to\folder',
    '.\path\to\folder',
    '.\path\to\folder',
    '.\path\to\folder',
    …
]);
~~~